File: The two are facing charges for corruption and the possession of illegal drugs. Wikimedia Commons JOHANNESBURG - A man and a woman have been arrested after they were caught with drugs worth R1.5-million in Klerksdorp. The woman aged 26 and a 33-year old man were arrested during an intelligence-driven operation on Friday. READ: 10 suspects arrested in cocaine bust It is believed the male suspect tried to bribe one of the police officers. The two are facing charges for corruption and the possession of illegal drugs. They will appear in the Klerksdorp Magistrates' Court on Monday.